<item>
            <title>[LU-2924] shrink ldlm_poold workload</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2924</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ldlm_poold wakes every second currently and walk list of all namespaces in the system doing some bookkeeping.&lt;br/&gt;
On systems with a lot of servers this client list gets quite large and it makes no sense to visit every namespace in the list if some of them don&apos;t actually have any locks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As such I think it makes sense to only get ldlm_poold to iterate over non-empty client namespaces.&lt;br/&gt;
Estimates from Fujitsu indicate that on a system with 2000 OSTs just the list iteration (i.e. empty namespaces) takes 2ms which is probably excessive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="17790">LU-2924</key>
            <summary>shrink ldlm_poold workload</summary>
